\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ interest and robbery. Whoever does not rejoice in his lot and is absorbed in amassing money, 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ eventually commits the sins of robbery, fraud, and taking interest. One who does not rejoice in his lot 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ concerning the love of his wife, has a passionate lust for women, and harbors erotic thoughts about 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ married women. \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ to eat and to drink\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  from what the Holy One, blessed be He, graciously granted him, 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ and to rejoice with his lot. And [according to] the Midrash Aggadah (Ecc. Rabbah 2:26): All mention 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ of eating and drinking in Ecclesiastes, refers only to the study of Torah, as it is stated (Isa. 55:1): “go, 
