\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ righteousness shall go before you.” \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ the days of his life that God gave him\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  he shall do so, and the end 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ of the verse is connected to its beginning, and it is a transposed verse, [to be interpreted thus:] there is 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ nothing better for man in the days of his life that God gave him than to eat, drink and rejoice, and that 
