\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ ultimately everyone will receive his just deserts. \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ one occurrence\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  And they know that the end of 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ everyone—whether righteous or wicked—is to die, and they all have one fate in this world. All this 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ they know, but nevertheless, they choose for themselves the good way, because they know that there 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ is a difference between them in the World to Come. \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ for the righteous\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  such as Noah. \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ and for the 
\lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ wicked\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  such as Pharaoh-Neco. This one became crippled, and that one became crippled. \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ for the good 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ This is Moses. \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ and for the pure\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  This is Aaron. \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ and for the unclean\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  These are the Spies. These 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ [Moses and Aaron] spoke well of the Land of Israel, but those spoke derogatorily about it. These did 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ not enter the Land, and those did not enter the Land; hence, they have one fate. \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ and for he who 
\lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ sacrifices\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  This is Josiah, as it is said: “And Josiah offered a sacrifice.” \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ and for he who does not 
\lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ sacrifice\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  This is Ahab, who caused Israel to refrain from performing the festival pilgrimages. This one 
